- `company` — who the employer is: overview, mission, history, size, "about us" culture prose, "why join us" value-prop paragraphs, references to the company website.
- `team` — the specific team / org unit this role sits in: product area, reporting line, team scope. Distinct from the whole-company `company` kind.
- `role` — what the person will do day-to-day: responsibilities, "what you'll do" bullets, project context, deliverables, onsite/remote role mentions that appear in role prose.
- `requirements` — must-have qualifications: years of experience, required skills, education, spoken languages, **physical demands** ("stand for 8 hrs", "lift 50 lbs", "vision"), background checks, driving licences, security clearance.
- `preferred` — explicitly-flagged nice-to-haves / "bonus points" / "preferred qualifications". Only use when the text itself labels them preferred, not merely implicit in a requirements list.
- `benefits` — concrete compensation + perks: salary/bonus prose, PTO, parental leave, healthcare, pension/retirement, remote/hybrid/visa policy, learning budget, gym, meals, specific employer-paid extras. **Not** generic "why join us" culture prose — that's `company`.
- `application` — mechanics of applying: how to apply, interview process, deadlines, relocation, recruiting-scam warnings, hiring-manager contact.
